Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Melt butter in medium skillet on medium heat. Add onions; cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, grill steak 5 minutes on each side or until medium doneness (160 degrees F). Stir steak sauce into onion mixture; cook an additional 5 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally. Cut steak into four pieces. Serve with the onion sauce.